1.5 We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
1.5.1 Coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer to confirm the status of the checks reported as outstanding checks to determine whether these were issued to the payees or cancelled checks;
1.5.2 Exert effort to review the long outstanding/stale checks and require the Municipal Treasurer to cancel the unclaimed stale checks and to furnish the Accounting Office with the original Disbursement Vouchers and its supporting documents, for the preparation of the Journal Entry Voucher, following the procedures prescribed to ensure recording of such cancellation;
1.5.3 Determine whether checks claimed by the payees were presented for payment, and secure the addresses of the payees for notification of the return of stale checks in their possession for replacement; and
1.5.4 Draw the JEV to restore the cash and liabilities pertaining to the stale checks to present fairly the recorded Cash in Bank and accounts payable accounts.

We recommended that Management:

a. Pursuant to COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, create an Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality, whether acquired through purchase or donation, including those constructed by administration and found at station;

b. Thru the Inventory Committee created, update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile with accounting records;

c. Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and 

d. After the inventory taking, direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the updated ledger cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to the Section 269 of the GAM for LGUs.

We recommended that Management:
Pursuant to COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, create an Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality, whether acquired through purchase or donation, including those constructed by administration and found at station;
Thru the Inventory Committee created, update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile with accounting records;
Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and
After the inventory taking, direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the updated ledger cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to the Section 269 of the GAM for LGUs.

We recommended that the Municipal Government adopt a system of payroll payment through the Automated Teller Machine (ATMs) of banks which would result in:

Convenience on the part of the Management since payroll payments are distributed from the payroll account maintained in an authorized government depository bank to the individual accounts of the employees;
Convenience on the part of the employees since payrolls can be withdrawn anytime in ATM during their free time and which was located near the Municipal Hall;
Decreases if not eliminates the risk of loss or misapplication of funds;
Reduces cash advances handled by the Disbursing Officer;
On time liquidation of cash advances.

